## Machine Learning Model Results

A Random Forest classification model was implemented to predict patient health risk levels using physiological indicators such as heart rate, blood pressure, oxygen saturation, temperature, and stress level.

The dataset was divided into training and testing sets using an 80:20 split. The trained model was evaluated using a confusion matrix and performance metrics.

